<h1>About This Site</h1>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<ol>
	<li>This site contains more than 300 pages of content from a wide variety of sources. Sources have been acknowledged at all places.</li>
	<li>Links have been provided to online books / material / websites wherever possible, so that an interested reader can access the links and order books online / offline.</li>
	<li>You can navigate this site through two methods.</li>
</ol>
<p>One, by clicking on the left and top navigation bars - the navigation bar to the left of the screen gives you access to the sections on the Ramakrishna Mission, Activities of the Nagpur Math, etc.; the navigation bar to the top gives you access to the lives and teachings of the Holy Trinity, all the Monastic Disciples of Sri Ramakrishna and some of the Householder Disciples.</p>
<p>Two, by clicking on the key images provided in the web-site. Many of the images such as the collage of Sri Ramakrishna and his disciples and the image of the Holy Trinity give you direct access to the respective sections dedicated to these personalities.</p>
<p>The aim of this dual navigation is to give you the choice to explore the lives and activities described in this site in the manner most suited to your taste.</p>
